def_cn: (常因疲惫或不愉快)不情愿地走
def_en: If you traipse somewhere, you go there unwillingly, often because you are tired or unhappy.

def_cn: 令人不快地走(或转悠);碍事地走(或转悠)
def_en: If you talk about people traipsing somewhere, you mean that they are going there or moving about there in a way that annoys someone or gets in their way.
